{"id":"math140-defint210-ia002","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Integration and Antiderivatives","subtopic":"Definite integrals","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A marginal revenue function is MR(x) = x^{n}. Find total revenue from x = {lo} to x = {hi} units.","params":{"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":2},"lo":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":1},"hi":{"type":"int","min":3,"max":6}},"answer_expr":"defint210","steps":["TR = integral from {lo} to {hi} of x^{n} dx = [x^{n+1}/({n+1})] from {lo} to {hi}.","= ({hi_pow} - {lo_pow}) / ({n+1}) = {answer_defint210}."],"tags":["business-calculus","total-revenue","definite-integral","marginal"]}
